ased","1350–Female":"1350–Deceased","1354–1406":"1354–1406","1320–1350":"1320–1350","1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1377":"1377","Abt 1320":"about 1320","1354":"1354","1420":"1420","1320":"1320","25 January 1350":"25 January 1350","1350":"1350","1406":"1406","Hermiston, Midlothian, Scotland":"Hermiston, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom","Dalkeith, Lothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Merchiston, Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Douglas","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from any of various places called from their situation on a river named with Gaelic <i>dubh</i> ‘dark, black’ + <i>glas</i> ‘stream’ (a derivative of <i>glas</i> ‘blue’). There are several localities in Scotland and Ireland so named, but the one from which the surname is derived in most if not all cases is Douglas in Lanarkshire 20 miles south of Glasgow, the original stronghold of the influential Douglas family and their retainers.","History: The family taking their name from Douglas in Lanarkshire were of Flemish origin. They rose to great prominence in the 14th and 15th centuries, controlling the earldoms of Douglas, Morton, and Angus, and later, Queensberry."],"variants":[{"name":"Douglass","meanings":["Scottish and English (Durham and Northumbria): variant of   Douglas  .","History: William Douglass, a physician recognized for his identification and description of an epidemic of scarlet fever, was born <i>c.</i> 1691 in Gifford, Haddington County, Scotland, and settled in Boston in 1718. The abolitionist, orator, and journalist Frederick Douglass assumed the name after escaping from slavery in 1838 and traveling to Massachusetts. Son of a white father and a slave with some Indian blood, he was born Frederick Augustus Washington Bailey <i>c.</i> 1817 in Tuckahoe, MD."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Douglas was born about 1320, in Hermiston, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom. He had at least 3 sons and 2 daughters. He died on 25 January 1350, in Merchiston, Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 31."},"et":{"Abt 1320–25 January 1350":"umbes 1320–25. jaanuar 1350","1325–1420":"1325–1420","1335–1377":"1335–1377","1348–Male":"1348–Surnud","1350–Female":"1350–Surnud","1354–1406":"1354–1406","1320–1350":"1320–1350","1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1377":"1377","Abt 1320":"umbes 1320","1354":"1354","1420":"1420","1320":"1320","25 January 1350":"25. jaanuar 1350","1350":"1350","1406":"1406","Hermiston, Midlothian, Scotland":"Hermiston, Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Dalkeith, Lothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Merchiston, Edinburgh, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1320–25 January 1350":"noin 1320–25. tammikuuta 1350","1325–1420":"1325–1420","1335–1377":"1335–1377","1348–Male":"1348–Kuollut","1350–Female":"1350–Kuollut","1354–1406":"1354–1406","1320–1350":"1320–1350","1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1377":"1377","Abt 1320":"noin 1320","1354":"1354","1420":"1420","1320":"1320","25 January 1350":"25. tammikuuta 1350","1350":"1350","1406":"1406","Hermiston, Midlothian, Scotland":"Hermiston, Midlothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dalkeith, Lothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Merchiston, Edinburgh, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1320–25 January 1350":"environ 1320–25 janvier 1350","1325–1420":"1325–1420","1335–1377":"1335–1377","1348–Male":"1348–Décédé","1350–Female":"1350–Décédée","1354–1406":"1354–1406","1320–1350":"1320–1350","1348":"1348","1325":"1325","1335":"1335","1377":